HEADWORD: Mourne
<hw>Mourne</hw> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧rn)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 2d
<er>Morne</er>.]</ety> <def>The armed or feruled end of a staff; in a
sheephook, the end of the staff to which the hook is attached.</def>
<rj><au>Sir P. Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
